# Sync Config

## Calendar ID

> Optional when authenticated via `flowdeck auth google` — defaults to `primary` (your main calendar).
> Set this to sync a specific calendar, or to a direct `.ics` URL / public Google Calendar ID for an unauthenticated read.
> Find the ID in Google Calendar → Settings → your calendar → "Calendar ID". Example: `yourname@gmail.com` or `abc123xyz@group.calendar.google.com`

{{CALENDAR_ID}}

## Public Source

> Optional. An additional read-only sync source — a public Google Calendar ID or a public ICS URL.
> Public GCals (e.g. holidays, sports seasons) are fetched via their public ICS feed.
> ICS URLs are fetched and parsed directly. Leave blank or keep the placeholder to disable.
> Public events are marked read-only in cards; use `send-to-gcal` to copy one to your own calendar.
> Example (US holidays): `en.usa#holiday@group.v.calendar.google.com`

{{PUBLIC_SOURCE}}

## Sync Range

> Default range used by `.flowdeck/.calendardeck/_sync/` (the sync standing card) when no explicit range is given.
> Examples: `current-month`, `next-30-days`, `2026-06-01–2026-06-30`

{{SYNC_RANGE}}

